---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Use Cases | BeaconGuard Regulated AI Operations"
  description="BeaconGuard workflow patterns for healthcare privacy review, financial services review, and regulated internal automation with ALLOW/DENY enforcement."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Use Cases</h1>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing applications for regulated enterprise workflows where probabilistic model behavior cannot serve as the authorization boundary.
      It evaluates trusted request context against an Active Verified Release and returns ALLOW or DENY before governed execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Priority workflow patterns</h2>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare privacy and operational AI review</h3>
        <p>Deterministic context tags, user role, source-system trust, and approved pathway requirements can be playbook-gated before AI-assisted work is allowed to proceed. Absent approval yields DENY with Execution Prevented.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial crime, fraud, and dispute review</h3>
        <p>AML, KYC, fraud, dispute, and account exception workflows can require approval before customer-impacting recommendations proceed. Missing approval is DENY, not permission via review.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated internal automation</h3>
        <p>Internal tools and agents touching regulated systems can be denied before action when controls or trust conditions fail. Verifiable Decision Records support governance follow-up without changing the DENY result.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Operational patterns</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Playbook-gated requests before governed execution</li>
      <li>Deterministic ALLOW or DENY at the Runtime Control Boundary</li>
      <li>DENY when approval is absent (illustrative reason style: <code>APPROVAL_REQUIRED</code>)</li>
      <li>Verifiable Decision Records for Evidence, Replay, and Verification</li>
      <li>Fail-closed handling when required release, trust, or freshness conditions are not met</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Regulated workflow focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is focused on regulated enterprise workflows where authorization, evidence, and control ownership remain explicit.
      It is not a generic AI governance consulting service, chatbot, model host, or GRC repository.
    </p>
  </section>

